23/06/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Local authorities confirmed on Monday (June 22nd) the first swine flu case in the country. 
Health Minister Miodrag Radunovic told a press conference that the patient is a 19-year-old Montenegrin student who returned a couple of days ago from the United States where he was studying. 
He is in stable condition. 
(RTCG, Mina, Tanjug, BTA, Reuters, DPA - 22/06/09)
